<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      input:invalid {
         color: red;
         border: 2px solid red;
      }
      input:valid {
         color: green;
         border: 2px solid green;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The :invalid CSS pseudo-class represents any &lt;input&gt; or other
   &lt;form&gt; element whose contents fail to validate. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   
   <form action="#">
      <label for="website-url"> Your Dream Website URL: </label>
      <input type="url" name="website-url" id="website-url">
      <br>
      <label for="email"> Your Email Address: </label>
      <input type="email" name="email" id="email">
   </form>
   <p> If the value is valid the <b>&lt;input&gt;</b> turns green. </p>
   <p> If the value is invalid the <b>&lt;input&gt;</b> turns red. </p>
</body>
</html>